Basic Chat Bot Project Documentation 🤖
1. Project Title

Basic Chat Bot Using Python

2. Introduction

A chatbot is a software application designed to simulate human conversation through text or voice interaction. Chatbots are widely used in customer support, virtual assistance, and automated communication systems.

This project focuses on developing a simple text-based chatbot using Python. The chatbot interacts with users by responding to predefined inputs and commands. The project helps beginners understand the fundamentals of conversational programming and user interaction handling.

3. Objective
To develop a simple chatbot using Python.
To understand chatbot working principles.
To implement conditional statements and loops.
To improve logical thinking and programming skills.
To create an interactive command-line application.
4. Technologies Used
Technology	Purpose
Python 3	Programming Language
CLI	User Interaction
5. Features
Interactive chatbot conversation
Predefined user responses
Simple and beginner-friendly design
Continuous conversation until exit command
Fast and lightweight implementation
6. System Requirements
Hardware Requirements
Minimum 2 GB RAM
Basic computer/laptop
Software Requirements
Python 3.x
VS Code / PyCharm / Any Python IDE
7. Working of the Project
The chatbot starts and greets the user.
The user enters a message or question.
The program checks the user input using conditions.
Based on the input:
The chatbot generates a predefined response.
The conversation continues in a loop.
The chatbot stops when the user enters an exit command.
